article.headline: Auburn 61, Bethune-Cookman 46
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. -- Guard Dewayne Reed came off the bench to score 14 points, leading the Tigers to a 61-46 win against Bethune-Cookman on Tuesday night. Auburn (3-1) held Bethune-Cookman to a 30.4 percent mark (17 of 56) from the field, and forced 12 turnovers. Reed was 3-for-5 on 3-pointers, and Quantez Robertson added 12 points and a team-high eight rebounds for the Tigers. Tay Waller, who was averaging 18.3 points per contest for the Tigers, finished scoreless for the night and was 0-for-6 shooting, all from 3-point range. Bethune-Cookman (1-3) had just 16 points at halftime, and shot 6-for-23 from behind the 3-point line. Jarrell Thomas scored 16 points to lead Bethune-Cookman. Auburn extended its 12-point lead to 56-33 late in the game before coach Jeff Lebo turned to his reserves. The 46 points allowed by Auburn was the third-fewest of Lebo's tenure.
